## What if, tariffs?
# A Synthetic Control Group approach to short-term impact assessment for policy evaluation - the case of EU tariff, on Chinese EV OEMs, impact on German EV vehicle sales 

## Overview

```

Statistics for Data Science is a first year, first semester course in the Masters for Data Science with specialization in Data Science, lectured at NovaIMS, this github hosts our teams project for that course - class of 2024.

Our aim is to analyze short-term demand trend shifts in EV in Germany, with respect to European Union tariffs dating July 1st, comparing the performance of a Multiple Linear Regression model (MLRM), vis. Synthetic Group Control (SGC). With this result, we wish to show tentative results that SGC can be a useful quantitative tool for decision makers in policy evaluation, that can provide insights even in low-information density environments.

```

## Project Structure

```

Statistics4DS/
├── .git/                     # Git repository metadata  
├── .gitignore                # Specifies files/folders to ignore in Git  
├── LICENSE                   # License file for the project  
├── README                    # Project documentation  
├── renv/                     # Directory created by renv for package management  
│   ├── library               # Installed packages (optional to include in Git)  
│   ├── staging               # Temporary staging area for package installation  
│   ├── activate.R            # Activation script for renv  
│   └── settings.json         # Configuration settings for renv  
├── renv.lock                 # Lock file for renv package management  
├── resources/                # Main directory for all supporting materials  
│   ├── references/           # Subdirectory for citation files  
│   ├── sources/              # Subdirectory for other source materials  
│   ├── past_projects/        # Subdirectory for previous project files  
│   └── supporting_literature/ # Optionally include this if you want to keep it separate  
├── _project/                 # Directory for your R project files  
│   ├── _figures/             # Directory for output figures from visualizations  
│   └── _scripts/             # Directory for organizing scripts  
│       ├── _analysis/        # Scripts for analysis  
│       ├── _markdown/        # Scripts for generating markdown reports  
│       ├── _preprocessing/   # Scripts for data preprocessing  
│       └── _visualizations/  # Scripts that create visualizations  
├── Statistics4DS.Rproj       # RStudio project file  

```

